Form-Validator is a lightweight and versatile JavaScript library designed to streamline and simplify the process of validating HTML forms. This library empowers developers to implement robust client-side validation, ensuring data integrity and improving user experience. With Form-Validator, you can effortlessly define validation rules for various form fields, including text inputs, email fields, password fields, and more. It supports a wide range of validation types such as required fields, email format validation, minimum and maximum length constraints, and custom validation functions. By integrating Form-Validator into your web projects, you can prevent invalid data from being submitted, reduce server-side processing, and provide real-time feedback to users, leading to a more efficient and user-friendly form submission process. While the core library is written in JavaScript for client-side validation, it can be easily integrated with any backend technology.

